title: North Korea, Thailand extend group leads in Asian qualifying
text:
North Korea, Thailand extend group leads in Asian qualifying By - Associated Press   
TOKYO (AP) - North Korea and Thailand had wins Tuesday to extend their group leads in the second round of Asian qualifying for the World Cup. 
Jong Il Gwan’s 12th-minute penalty gave the North Koreans a 1-0 win at Pyongyang in Group H, and Thailand beat Vietnam 3-0 at Hanoi with goals from Kroekrit Thaweekarn in the 29th , skipper Theeraton Bunmathan in the 70th and an own-goal from Dinh Tien Thanh to move five points clear in Group F. 
In other early matches, Malaysia beat winless East Timor at Dili for its first win in Group A, striker Chan Siu Ki scored in the 89th to give Hong Kong a 1-0 win over Bhutan in Group C, Singapore held off Cambodia 2-1 to join Japan atop Group E and Turkmenistan held off Guam 1-0 in Group D. 
The eight group winners and four best runners-up will advance to the last round of Asian qualifying. 
Australia, Japan, South Korea, Iran and China were among the teams not playing Tuesday.
